id: pm-ltbr
title: Extension FlagDefinition lacks 'list' and 'default' fields — extension-registered flags cannot match core comma-list contract
description: "The FlagDefinition interface in extension-types.ts (line 398) has: long, short, value_name, description, required, enabled, visible, type/value_type, plus an index signature `[key: string]: unknown`. The core CliFlagContract in cli-contracts.ts has an additional `list?: boolean` field (used by coalesceRepeatedListFlags) and there is no `default` field. An extension that registers a comma-list flag via registerFlags cannot declare list:true to get the same accumulation behavior as core flags (e.g. `--tags`). This means multi-value extension flags lose values on repeated invocations. The `[key: string]: unknown` index signature silently accepts list:true but it is not documented, typed, or enforced."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
tags[4]: "area:extensions","area:sdk",bug,dx
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:06:01.144Z"
